posts.title: Visual Aesthetics: Dynamic Visual Expression Under Cyberpunk Style (Assisted by Gemini Ai)
posts.content: With Cyberpunk as its core visual tone, this website creates a visual experience that combines a sense of technology and dynamic interactivity through the in-depth integration of visual parameters and multimedia elements. The specific design highlights are as follows: I. Core Visual Parameter Settings The website defines visual output effects through clear visual control parameters to ensure style consistency and detailed accuracy: Pixel Density (PIXEL_DENSITY: 6): A medium pixel density setting is adopted. While retaining the unique "digital graininess" of the cyberpunk style, it also takes into account the display clarity of different devices â€” avoiding image blurriness caused by low pixel density and preventing excessive weakening of style recognition due to high pixel density. It is compatible with the visual presentation needs of desktop and tablet devices. Bass Color Reaction (BASS_COLOR_REACT: 50 2): Realizes the interactive linkage between audio and vision. When the background audio (y2k_track.mp3) is played, the bass frequency will trigger dynamic color changes. Among them, "50" represents the sensitivity threshold of color response, and "2" corresponds to the dual-tone linkage mode (presumably the alternating or overlapping of classic cyberpunk neon blue and magenta dual tones), making the vision "rhythm" with the audio tempo and enhancing the immersive experience. II. Functional Design: Experience Architecture Centered on "Audio-Visual Interaction" The website's functions revolve around "immersive audio-visual experience", taking into account basic browsing and dynamic interaction needs. The core functional modules are as follows: (I) Core Interactive Function: Audio-Visual Linkage Audio-Driven Visual Dynamics: The core function is "bass color reaction". When users play audio, the page background color or visual elements will change with the bass rhythm (such as alternating light and dark colors, changes in the flicker frequency of color blocks). This breaks the "one-way browsing" mode of traditional static web pages, transforming users from "passive viewing" to "active perception" and enhancing user participation. Multimedia Control Entrance: It is presumed to include basic control elements such as audio play/pause buttons and volume adjustment sliders. The control components are designed in a cyberpunk style (such as neon borders and glowing effects when hovering), which is consistent with the overall vision and avoids the "sense of abruptness" of functional components. III. Code Architecture: Lightweight and Highly Interactive Technical Implementation With the core goal of "realizing audio-visual linkage", the website's code architecture adopts a lightweight front-end technology stack, balancing functional stability and development efficiency. The presumed architecture is as follows: (I) Core Front-End Technology Stack Basic Framework: Centered on HTML5 + CSS3 + JavaScript.
